{[showcards S:ST]

You are South. The bidding has been as shown. You led the \H4, North plays the \HJ, won by East with \HA.

East plays the \SJ, you follow with \S5, dummy \S3 and North plays the \S2. East continues with the \ST 

Play the \S6.

North's \S2 tells you he had an ODD number of \Ss, obviously 3. Since East also must have 3, you must take your \SA on the third round, depriving dummy of the extra \S trick.

East may now turn to the \D suit, but your side can win the first \D and drive out East's \HK. You will win 2 \Hs, 2 \Ds and the \SA, down 1}
[Play "W"]H4

